projects.description: Covid-19 vaccine appointments in India have become scarce and difficult to make. With the rush of people trying to get a slot, getting it manually using CoWin or Arogya Setu has become and ardous task. This node.js app intends to remedy that. Using puppeteer it commands a headless Chromium instance and polls the cowin-api as much as 50 times in a minute (bypasing the rate limit of 100 calls/ 5 min for the public API) by calling a private API endpoint and simulating real user interaction. It looks for available vaccination sessions in the district you supply in the config file in the next six days and sends you an email notifying you available slots as and when they become available.
projects.title: covid-vaccine-appointment-finder

projects.description:
Simple file picker that lets users pick files from a directory tree. Supports navigation inside a nested file structure and allows for customizations such as filtering files based on extension and custom icons for different file types. Can be used as the UI for accessing the file system of a file server that has the navigation logic built into it, you just need to pass into it a function that will return the directory entries for a given path. Compatible with the directory-tree generated by node-file-tree-explorer on the server side.

documentation : https://github.com/SwapnilB31/react-file-picker

projects.description: Book My Vaccine is an android app created with React-Native that helps you find and book available covi19-vaccine slots in your area. It has an alert feature that lets users run a background service that queries the CoWIN Public API periodically for a user selected district/postal area and pushes a local notification as and when slots become available. It also supports Auto Sign In (App reads SMS OTP and signs you in), Beneficiary Management and In-App Appointment Scheduling.
projects.title: BookMyVaccine

projects.description:
SmallWorks is a Services Aggregator that provides various household services like cleaning, painting, refurbishing, upholstery. electrical and electronics repairs to its users. Besides the service offerings the platform also offers Maintenance Packages that provide, weekly, monthly, quarterly maintenance of their furniture, household items, gadgets and or vehicles. We provide real time geographical tracking of goods and services that lets users follow their order all the way through. Once the user places and order, an estimated cost is presented to the user for the said service/repair, which is processed further if the user accepts the estimate. After which the order is sent to the workers, and is picked up and completed by one of the workers registered on our platform. Workers get turn by turn navigation to the  work site (Google Maps API) on the SmallWorks Partner App. Where they can track their progress, payments, goals and milestones. The Administration module provides functions such as inventory, asset, stock, area, location, catalogue, employee, payment management etc.

Technology Stack Used: MongoDB, MySQL, Node.js, Express.js, Bootstrap4, Apache Cordova, Google Maps API, Google Speech API, AWS EC2
projects.title: SmallWorks - Home Services Aggregator
